1 month postpartum 👶🏼💙 Your core consists of many different parts that work together as stabilizers and movers and YES, it’s much more than just your abs. Your core is stretched and weakened during pregnancy so it is important to focus on your deep core postpartum to regain strength and proper function.  Doing crunches etc will actually hurt you more than help you. Think of it as building a house without a frame, you must start with the deep core first. Remember that everyone’s pregnancy and postpartum recovery timeline is different, so chat with a doctor before you exercise. Give yourself grace and time to heal! Just look at  what you created 👶🏼🥹 
I started with breath work and slowly added the rest in! I do 1 minute each exercise 💙

‘In Sardinia, I had the good fortune of meeting the Melis family who holds the Guinness World Record as the oldest family in history. They are nine siblings whose collective age was 851 years (the oldest was 109). They ate the same lunch every day:  sourdough bread, a glass of Blue Zones Cannonau wine, and a very special minestrone.

Minestrone is simply a soup made from available garden vegetables, beans, and grain (usually a type of pasta). The combination yields a delicious one-bowl meal that is high in protein and most importantly, a potpourri of fibers and fuel your microbiome’ -@bluezones 

If you have never read about the blue zones, it is so interesting! Certain areas in the world where people statistically live longer. Lifestyle, time outdoors, family, community, good food etc seem to be common factors. 

⁣
½ cup dry garbanzo beans⁣
½ cup dry white beans⁣
½ cup dry pinto or red beans⁣
1.5 cups 1-2”  cubed potatoes⁣
½ cup of pearl barley (not quick cook)⁣
Approx 4 cups of veg stock ( more if you like it soupier)
1 medium onion, chopped⁣
5 stalks celery chopped finely 
5 carrots, chopped⁣
8 cloves garlic, chopped,⁣
2 Bay Leaves⁣
1 tsp oregano (I used fresh) ⁣
2 tbs olive oil⁣
1 tsp red or black pepper (red makes it hotter)⁣
1 – 14 oz can of chopped tomatoes or 5 Roma tomatoes⁣
Salt to taste⁣
⁣
You can use canned beans but I like dry! If using dry beans soak them over night in water. ⁣
Add all veggies and olive oil to a soup pot and cook until onion is clear. Add tomatoes, beans, broth, spices, barley (or noodle)Turn to low and cook until beans are soft!!! Salt and pepper to taste. I love to add nutritional yeast and kale to mine, if adding- add when finished cooking! Thank you @bluezones for sharing this! 🫶

I did a similar workout 
with some of my clients and it’s SO GOOD. ⁣
More reps = lighter weight. ⁣
Less reps = heavier weight. ⁣
So for example you could use 6,8,10, pound dumbbells. ⁣
When you have 12 reps you use the 6 lb dumbbells. ⁣
10 reps you use 8 pound dumbbells etc. ⁣
Do 12 reps, then 10, then 8, then 10, then 12. 
Complete all exercises and then start with the next amount of reps! 
if you only have two sets of dumbbells, that is perfectly fine, work with what you have.⁣
Don’t forget to do that many reps on the right and left where applicable.

I made a full jar of this last month and dare I say I think it really works! Garlic and honey have been shown to have antibacterial and antiviral properties. Also high in antioxidants! To make fermented garlic & honey: 
Place whole garlic cloves in a sterile jar ( some people smash the cloves slightly) pour honey (I use raw unfiltered) over the raw garlic until the garlic is fully covered. Seal it and let it sit for 3-4 days. Open and stir (youll probably see little bubbles and that means it’s fermenting) reseal and use in a month! 
Can be used as a salad dressing, marinade or by the spoonful when you’re not feeling well. 
Not for babies or kids under 2 years. This is a holistic approach to cold/flu season so make sure to ask a doc.

This soup on repeat all Fall/Winter 
Recipe : 
9-11 Roma tomatoes 
1 red pepper 
5 garlic cloves 
1/2 yellow onion 
2 sprigs Fresh oregano 
Olive oil, salt and pepper 
2 cups veggie broth 
1 cup coconut milk 
( would be wonderful with basil as well) 

Chop all veggies and spread on a baking pan. Drizzle with olive oil, salt, pepper and fresh oregano. Cover with foil and cook at 450 for 35 minutes. Once cooked add veggies to a soup pot with broth and coconut milk. Use immersion blender or transfer soup to blender and blend. Simmer in soup pot for 10 ish minutes. Serve with fresh oregano  and maybe a grilled cheese 🥰🍅🌿

Pumpkin chili 🌶️🎃🫘: Nothing screams fall like pumpkin and if you’re anything like me you probably have a can or two that you have no clue what to do with! Well here you go- 
1 yellow onion diced 
5 garlic cloves minced 
2 sweet potatoes cubed 
1 can of corn 
1 can of pinto beans 
1 can of black beans 
1 can of chopped tomatoes 
1 can of pumpkin purée 
2 cups of broth ( I used veggie) 
2 tbsp of your fav taco seasoning ( I like @traderjoes and @sietefoods ) 

How to: Throw everything into a crockpot and cook on high for 4-6 hours. Finish with salt and pepper! Top with cilantro and maybe some cheese / sour cream!
*if you don’t have a crockpot cook the onion and garlic in a soup pot, add the sweet potato and cook for a few minutes then add everything else and simmer until potatoes are cooked!

Butternut squash Mac 🫶. 
One white onion 
One butternut squash deseeded and cubed 
5 to 6 garlic cloves peeled 
One sprig of rosemary 
2 cups of veg/ chicken broth 
1/2 cup nutritional yeast
One can of coconut milk
One box of pasta
Salt and pepper/olive oil 
Could also use fresh grated cheese at the end instead of nutritional yeast! I would suggest Parmesan or cheddar. 
This makes a lot of this ‘cheese’ sauce so use a lot of pasta or you may have a bit left over!!!

Preheat your oven to 450. Chop all veggies and place them on a foil lined baking tray. Top with rosemary olive oil and salt and pepper. Cook the veggies in the oven for 30 minutes. Take the cooked veggies and put them in a blender with the coconut milk, veggie broth and nutritional yeast. Cook your pasta and drain. Add your cheese sauce to your pasta and salt and pepper!

Instagram cut this video in half BUT the details are below- Longevity soup round 2 🍛🍅🧄🫶
You HAVE to try this. The miso gives it so much flavor and the noodles make it fun for the kids. Presley says, “there’s bows in it!’ 

Ingredients: 
5 carrots chopped 
5 stalks celery chopped 
3-5 garlic cloves minced 
Yellow onion chopped 
Yellow squash chopped 
Potatoes chopped ( your choice I did 6 red potatoes) 
1 can ( or 1/2 cup dry) garbanzo beans 
1 can ( or 1/2 cup dry) navy beans 
1 cup uncooked barley 
1 can or 4 large tomato’s chopped 
2 cups bow tie noodles (or any noodle) 
10 cups or 80 oz of broth of choice 
2 tbsp white miso paste ( don’t skip this) 
1 tbsp 21 seasoning salute from Trader Joe’s or any Italian seasoning 

Recipe: chop all veggies. Add carrots celery onion and garlic to a soup pot with a little bit of olive oil. Let cook on medium heat for five minutes and then add your potatoes and squash. Add your miso paste, seasoning, barley, beans and broth. Bring to a boil and add your noodles. Cover pot and lower heat and let cook for 20 minutes. Check to see that potatoes and veggies are cooked too soft! Add more broth if you wish, I like my soup a little bit thicker. Add salt/ pepper and enjoy!!! 
Makes a large batch! Cute recipe in half if you’d like.
*** if you are using dried beans you will want this to simmer for about 45 minutes to an hour.
